bio.experienceSummary:
Hello Families
My name is Melanie and I can be described as a very loving, patient and caring person! I have plenty of classroom experience as I have worked in special education, general education and after school programs as well as tutoring services classroom settings! I am very passionate about working with children to help them grow. I love to get creative with arts and crafts and other hands on activities! bio.experienceSummary: Hello wonderful families I am an experienced and nurturing child care provider with a genuine love for helping children learn, grow, and thrive. With 6+ years of experience, I excel in creating engaging and educational activities that promote development and creativity. Skilled in providing a safe and nurturing environment where children feel supported and encouraged to trust me as their provider. Dedicated to fostering positive relationships with both children and parents, ensuring open communication and trust. I take pride in knowing I can help families when they need someone to count on. I drive as well with over 15+ years of driving experience so you can feel safe with me driving your children to school, doctor's appointments or daily activities. I also love to cook any meals that would need to be cooked if so. I also am available for overnights, nanny, or even if you just need a few hours of my services. I hope I can help your family with my excellent services.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a devoted, professional and highly skilled nanny with 10 years experience of caring for children (Newborn - 14 yrs). I am very passionate about providing exceptional care. I excel in fostering creativity through engaging activities, ensuring nutritional well being, and maintaining a structured yet nurturing routine.

It brings me joy to watch children grow, learn, and develop, and I consider it a privilege to be a part of their journey. Being a nanny is not just a job for me. Your child's well being and happiness are my top priorities. My commitment is to always create a safe, loving, and stimulating environment for your children. 

I look forward to the opportunity to bring my experience, skills, and heartfelt commitment to your family, making a positive impact on your child's life.

Resume/References available upon request.

description.originalText: Amazing, trustworthy, punctual, dependable, energetic, caring, organized and very passionate are the perfect words I’d use to describe Jazz. Best of luck hun!

bio.experienceSummary: I am a writer and translator with a Masters of Fine Arts degree in Fiction Creative Writing, and I lived in Armenia this last year teaching English on a Fulbright. I have more than 5 years of experience working with kids. I have been babysitting children ages 2 to 8 since I was in high school, and I have been a camp counselor at art summer camps and special needs camps. I have also taught classes in high schools, ranging in topics from Health to Creating Writing. I can help with travel, summer homework, swimming supervision and more. I am very good at engaging children by inventing games, breaking out the pencils and the markers, building with legos, knitting, crocheting, and painting, and even doing fun writing exercises. I would love to get to know you and your kids better!

Hi, I'm Lara! I graduated from MSU in 2020 and had been working a corporate job since. I'm now in NYC nannying. Ive been in charge of meal prepping, housekeeping, bath time, taking kids to and from activities, play dates, etc. I've babysat the last 10 years, ages ranging from 3-month-old- 12 years old. I'm extremely flexible and always looking to work extra hours too :) Please let me know if you're interested!
